<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,789]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis box="[199,317,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name (Sankrit: 
<emphasis box="[672,747,621,644]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Dwipa</emphasis>
meaning 
<collectingCountry box="[868,938,620,645]" name="Iceland" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Island</collectingCountry>
) alludes to the insular distribution of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="111" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,789]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,692,717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[325,443,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dwipae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[325,443,692,717]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">H. dwipae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[453,546,692,717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[453,546,692,717]" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Knight" authorityName="Knight" box="[764,966,692,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pronus">
<emphasis box="[764,878,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">H. pronus</emphasis>
Knight
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1041,1231,692,717]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
but differs in the shape of the apices of the aedeagal shafts. Each aedeagal shaft, in lateral view, has 
<taxonomicName box="[1084,1213,727,752]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Amaranthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="10" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangular">a triangular</taxonomicName>
expansion which is not the case in 
<taxonomicName box="[319,430,765,788]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pronus">
<emphasis box="[319,430,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">H. pronus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and also the shaft is strongly sinuate in 
<taxonomicName box="[878,990,765,788]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pronus">
<emphasis box="[878,990,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">H. pronus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared to that in 
<taxonomicName box="[1220,1335,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dwipae">
<emphasis box="[1220,1240,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1254,1335,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="111">dwipae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
